SSG LIBRARY USED BY THE PAYROLL SYSTEM	  DEC. 03,1979

ZABORT - fn.abort%
	standard report abort function

ZBRACKET - fn.bracket$(number,left.digits%,cents%)
	Returns a format string which places a negative number in
	brackets (<0.00> or <0> if cents% set to false). If the number
	input is positive the bracket positions are filled by blanks

ZCKDIGIT - fn.ck.dig$(no$)
	returns a single check digit calculated from no$

ZCOMMON - standard common area for SSG	programs
	has chained.from.root%,common.drive$,common.date$, etc.

ZCONFIRM - fn.confirmed%
	TYPE "RUN" TO CONTINUE   TYPE "STOP" TO STOP PROGRAM

ZCONST - equates for all systems - required by DMS functions

ZDATEINC - I don't know what this is.

ZDATEIO - fn.date.in$, fn.date.out$
	fn.date.in$  takes yr%,mo%,dy%	and returns a internal date
			string (YYMMDD)
	fn.date.out$ takes an internal string (YYMMDD) and returns it
		as MM/DD/YY  , DD/MM/YY  etc. depending on the parameter file
		fields pr1.date.mo%, pr1.date.dy%, pr1.date.yr%

ZDMS - dms functions except init, clear, and attribute changes
	all return trash% except as noted
	zdmssca -   fn.crt.sca$(row%, column%)
		returns a string to set the cursor address to row%, column%
		used by other dms functions
	zdmsmsg -   fn.msg%(text$)
		displays text$ on standard message line
	zdmsemsg -  fn.emsg%(emsg%)
		calls fn.msg% using EMSG$(emsg%) as text
	zdmslit -   fn.lit%(id%)
		displays field(id%) as a literal, sets usage to true
	zdmsput -   fn.put%(value$, id%)
		displays formatted value$ at field id%
		stores value for refresh
	zdmsptal -  fn.put.all%(i.o%)
		displays all used output (literal) fields using fn.lit%
		if i.o%, displays all I/O (data entry) fields using fn.put%
	zdmsget -   fn.get%(ctl.mask%, id%)
		gets data at field id%, uses crt.ctl.mask$(ctl.mask%) as
		list of acceptable control characters. (valid data is always
		accepted, screen refresh and backspace are handled internally)
		CONTROL CHARACTER LISTS
			crt.ctl.mask$(1)= ctl.stopit$
			crt.ctl.mask$(2)= crt.ctl.mask$(1)+ctl.cr$+ctl.back$
			crt.ctl.mask$(3)= crt.ctl.mask$(2)+ctl.cancel$
			crt.ctl.mask$(4)= crt.ctl.mask$(2)+ctl.next$+ctl.save$+ctl.adding$
			crt.ctl.mask$(5)= crt.ctl.mask$(4)+ctl.delete$
			crt.ctl.mask$(6)= crt.ctl.mask$(2)+ctl.next$

		RETURNS:in.len% - length of input
			in$  - input string, null if in.status%<> req.valid%
			in.uc$- upper case of input string, or null
			in.status% -	req.valid%
					req.stopit%
					req.cr%
					req.back%
					req.cancel%
					req.next%
					req.save%
					req.adding%
					req.delete%
	12/02/79 all dms functions nolisted

ZDMSABRT - fn.abort%
	cursor addressed report interrupt function
	returns true if stop requested
	12/02/79 clears itself before exit

ZDMSBRT - fn.set.brt%(t.f%, id%)
	sets or clears brightness attribute for field specified

ZDMSCLR - fn.clr%(id%)
	clears specified field
	if a literal field, sets to unused
	if a data entry field, clears data buffer used for screen refresh
	11/18/79 sets any field cleared to not used

ZDMSCNST - equates for dms functions
	11/18/79 added ctl mask 6 (see notes for ZDMS)

ZDMSCOMM - common area to pass DMS variables from one program to another

ZDMSCONF - fn.confirmed%
	requests operator confirmation to continue, returns true
	if continuation requested, false if stop requested
	12/02/79 clears message line upon exit

ZDMSEMSG - fn.emsg%(emsg%)

ZDMSEOL  -  fn.crt.eol%(row%, column%)
	requires zdms
	erases from row, column to the end of the line

ZDMSGET - fn.get%(ctl.mask%, id%)
	gets input at screen field id%, uses control character mask ctl.mask%
	to limit acceptable control characters
	11/12/79 sets in.uc$ correctly
	11/18/79 clears message line upon exit
	12/02/79 clears message based on flag

ZDMSHAZL - fn.crt.initialize%(file$, disk$)
	quick CRT initialize for Hazeltine 1500

ZDMSINIT - fn.crt.initialize%(file$, disk$)
	initializes dms system
	sets crt characteristics to hazeltine 1500
	returns if file$ is null, or if not
	     searches for file$+".DEF" on the disk specified
	     resets crt characteristics to those specified by the file
	returns 0 - sucess
		1 - file not found
		2 - file is not correct format

ZDMSLIT - fn.lit%(id%)
	displays literal specified, sets attribute to used

ZDMSMSG - fn.msg%(text$)
	displays text$ on standard message line
	12/02/79 sets global flag that message issued

ZDMSPTAL - fn.put.all%(i.o%)
	puts all literals that are currently used on screen using fn.lit%
	if i.o% then puts all used io fields on screen using fn.put%
	11/13/79 fixed to refresh all fields correctly

ZDMSPUT - fn.put%(value$, id%)
	displays value$ in id field position
	11/13/79 fixed SB error on string display
	11/18/79 sets id% attribute to used
	12/03/79 treats an output only field as a string field

ZDMSRST - fn.reset%
	clears screen, resets to background
	12/03/79 fixed to set background correctly

ZDMSSCA - fn.crt.sca$(r%,c%) fn.crt.sca.row$(r%) fn.crt.sca.column$(c%)
	returns a string which will set a cursor address

ZDMSTEST - fn.test%(bit%, id%)
	tests attribute bit specified

ZDMSUSED - fn.set.used%(t.f%, id%)
	sets usage of field id% to used or not used based on t.f%

ZDRIVE - fn.get.drive%(desc$)
	requires ZINPUT
	uses fn.input%	to get a drive reference A-Z  Allows cr%

ZDSPYORN -  fn.dsp.yorn$(boolean.value%)
	returns "Y" if  value% is true, "N" if value is false

ZEDITDTE - fn.leap.year%(year%), fn.edit.date%(date$)
	requires ZNUMBER, ZPARSE
	fn.leap.year% is used by fn.edit.date%
	fn.edit.date% takes an external form date and converts it
	to 3 integers:	mo%,dy%,yr%  using the parameter specified
	date form fields as a guide. (parsing either as MM/DD/YY or
	DD/MM/YY)

ZEOJ - standard end of job for all programs except for sytem menu drivers
	it prints cursor addressed EOJ messages and sets common.return.code%
	to 0, 1, 2  for normal, error, premature EOJ
	11/18/79 changed 999.2 message
	12/02/79 uses function name instead of program name
		 prints abort on line 23

ZFILCONV - file name functions
	fn.drive.in%(temp$) converts @,a,b,c,d to 0,1,2,3,4
	fn.drive.out$(temp%) converts 0,1,2,3,4 to @,A,B,C,D
	fn.file.name.out$(c.name$,c.type$,c.drive%,c.password$,c.params$)
	provides a file name properly constructed. c.password$,c.params$ use
	undefined at present

ZFLIP	 - fn.name.flip$(name$)
	converts last name*first name  to  first name last name

ZGETDATE - fn.get.date$(description$)
	includes ZEDITDTE, ZDATEI/O
	requires ZNUMBER,ZPARSE for zeditdte,  ZINPUT
	uses fn.input%, fn.edit.date%, fn.date.in$ to input a valid date
	and return it in internal form

ZHEADING - fn.hdr%(report$)
	requires ZSTRING, ZDATEI/O
	prints a standard report heading, including company name,
	date, and the report name string used as a parameter.
	returns a line count

ZINPUT -	fn.input%(desc$,length%)
	uses an input line to get input, uses  "ENTER " and the description
	string parameter as a prompt. If the length parameter is < 255, the
	string input is disallowed if longer than the length specified.
	global variables cr% and stopit%  are set if the response is carriage
	return and "stop" or escape  respectively. If double quotes,
	line feeds, or ctl Z's are imbedded in the input string, the
	global flag invalid% is set to true.
	The function returns a true if any of the global flags are set.

ZNUMBER - fn.num%(number$)
	uses the match function to find any non-numeric characters if the
	string parameter

ZNUMERIC - fn.numeric%(number$,left.digits%,right.digits%)
	includes ZNUMBER
	checks that the string parameter contains only numeric characters
	except for a single decimal point, and that the number of characters
	on either side of the decimal point are within the limit specified

ZPARSE - fn.parse%(data$,delimiter$)
	parses the string parameter into the dimensioned variable
	token$(1), incrementing the subscript each time the delimiter string
	is encountered.  Token$(x) is dimensioned to 5 elements if token.limit%
	is not set to a different value the first time the function is called.

ZSERIAL - Serial number check

ZSTRING - fn.spread$(string$,amt%), fn.pad$(string$,n%),
 fn.center%(string$,width%)
	fn.spread$ pads each character in the string parameter with the
	number of blanks specified in the amount parameter
	fn.pad$ returns a string of the left-most n% characters of
	string parameter and a blank string.
	fn.center returns a tab value which will center the input string
	on a page of width width%.

ZSYSDRIV - fn.get.sys.drive%
	looks for file system$+"pr1.101" on drives A and B.
	returns A, B or a null string

ZYORN	-   fn.yorn%(cr.default%)
	does input line, no prompt
	returns true if yes, false if no, cr.default% if cr
	does not set any global flags for stop or back
